This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.DL (Digital Libraries) because it discusses bibliometric indicators and their correlation with research performance. It may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) because of the focus on citation-based metrics. Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CY (Computational Biology), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as these fields also use bibliometric indicators to evaluate research performance.
